In total, six carriages are alight at platforms 17 and 18. CAPE TOWN - Two trains have been burning at Cape Town station on Tuesday. In total, six carriages are alight at platforms 17 and 18. Four fire engines and 24 firefighters are in attendance. There have been train fires on an almost weekly basis across the city and Metrorail  has in most cases confirmed it believes arson is at play. Authorities have been struggling to make arrests and have hatched several plans to deal with the problem and other safety and security concerns on the rail network.  